cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper presents a technique for learning control Lyapunov functions, which are commonly used in control systems and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as a learner and a verifier, to infer and validate the candidate functions, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper uses nonlinear MPC controllers as demonstrators, which could also suggest a fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
